{"id":"quant-ph/0509100","submitter":"Matthias Kleinmann","authors":"M. Kleinmann, H. Kampermann, T. Meyer, D. Bruss","title":"Physical Purification of Quantum States","comments":"5 pages, 1 figure; published version","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. A 73, 062309 (2006)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.73.062309","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We introduce the concept of a physical process that purifies a mixed quantum\nstate, taken from a set of states, and investigate the conditions under which\nsuch a purification map exists. Here, a purification of a mixed quantum state\nis a pure state in a higher-dimensional Hilbert space, the reduced density\nmatrix of which is identical to the original state. We characterize all sets of\nmixed quantum states, for which perfect purification is possible. Surprisingly,\nsome sets of two non-commuting states are among them. Furthermore, we\ninvestigate the possibility of performing an imperfect purification.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Sep 2005 15:30:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 9 Mar 2006 15:01:58 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 12 Jun 2006 11:57:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
